  "body": "Well, no, but look!\r\n\r\n[Documentation for .flat](https://docs.perl6.org/type/Pair#(Any)_method_flat):\r\n\r\n> Please note that .flat will not solve the halting problem for you. If you flat an infinite list ``.flat`` may return that infinite list, eating all your RAM in the process.\r\n\r\nOK, let's see.\r\n\r\nCode:\r\n```perl6\r\nmy @x = 1, 3 … *; say @x.flat\r\n```\r\n\r\nResult:\r\n```\r\n(...)\r\n```\r\n\r\nTurns out it works just fine with infinite things? Then why all these scary stories if there's no issue? When exactly does it reify stuff if it does ever?",
